    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.7.0-dev+1299-g773516365-dirty\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nGentoo\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nKonsole 21.08.3\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nPortage (9999 Nightly)\n\n### How to reproduce the issue\n\n[Running modified nvim-qt frontend to demonstrate issue]\r\n\r\nThe following patch has been applied to instrument `mode_change` events:\r\n```patch\r\ndiff --git a/src/gui/shell.cpp b/src/gui/shell.cpp\r\nindex c91097b..1a469d1 100644\r\n--- a/src/gui/shell.cpp\r\n+++ b/src/gui/shell.cpp\r\n@@ -566,6 +566,7 @@ void Shell::handleRedraw(const QByteArray& name, const QVariantList& opargs)\r\n        } else if (name == \"mouse_off\"){\r\n                handleMouse(false);\r\n        } else if (name == \"mode_change\"){\r\n+               qDebug() << opargs;\r\n                handleModeChange(opargs);\r\n        } else if (name == \"set_title\"){\r\n                handleSetTitle(opargs);\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n1. Open GUI frontend: `nvim-qt -- -u NORC`\r\n2. Enter terminal mode with `:terminal`\r\n3. Notice no mode_change is reported for terminal mode.\r\n\r\nHere is a trace of all mode_change events:\r\n```\r\n(QVariant(QByteArray, \"normal\"), QVariant(qulonglong, 0))\r\n(QVariant(QByteArray, \"normal\"), QVariant(qulonglong, 0))\r\n(QVariant(QByteArray, \"normal\"), QVariant(qulonglong, 0)) // Occurs during startup\r\n(QVariant(QByteArray, \"cmdline_normal\"), QVariant(qulonglong, 4)) // : - Command mode entered\r\n(QVariant(QByteArray, \"normal\"), QVariant(qulonglong, 0)) // :terminal command completes\r\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThere should be a `mode_change` when the user enters and exits terminal mode.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nThere is no `mode_change` event, and the frontend cannot detect when the user is in terminal mode.\r\n\r\nRelated issues:\r\nhttps://github.com/equalsraf/neovim-qt/issues/999\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/19265",
